RIFTSMUD WIZARD STAFF OVERVIEW

AetherMUD uses five wizard ranks. position is canonical; wiz_role is the
display tag synced from position.

ROLE          POSITION      HELP TOPIC
Apprentice    apprentice    help apprentice *wizard staff
Admin         arch          help admin *wizard staff
Domain        domain_wiz    help domain *wizard staff
Coding        creator       help coding *wizard staff
Roleplay      rp_wiz        help roleplay *wizard staff

PROMOTION
1. makewiz <player>     -> Apprentice + apprentice kit
2. Apprentice picks a track in kit and submits the track task
3. Domain reviews (dominate -> Apprentice submissions)
   RP/Coding approved work goes to the coding queue (review on creation staff)
4. Domain/coding mark ready_for_setrole
5. Admin: setrole <player> <admin|domain|coding|rp>

First promotion from mortal creates:
  /realms/<name>/workroom.c
  /realms/<name>/area/{room,npc,weap,armor}/
Apprentices get the kit, not role staff. setrole grants role tools.

COMMAND MODEL
  Apprentice: kit + ambassador file tools
  Admin: full admin + creator commands
  Domain, Coding, RP: ambassador file tools + staff tool verbs only
  Coding QCS: staff of creation required
  Manual file editing: ed/cat/ls via ambassador path for all wizards

IN-GAME QUICK REFERENCE
Type read book in your workroom for a short role summary.

